  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>By 9th level, every eldritch cannon you create is more destructive:</p><ul><li>The cannon's damage rolls and temporary hit points granted all increase by 1d8.</li><li>If the cannon is force to make an ability check, or a saving throw, threat all its ability scores as 10 (+0) plus your proficiency modifier.</li><li>As an action, you can command the cannon to detonate if you are within 60 feet of it. Doing so destroys the cannon and forces each creature within 20 feet of it to make a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC, taking a number of d8s equal to half your artificer level in force damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</li></ul>",
